definition.value: A phenothiazine substituted at position 2 (para to the S atom) by a methylsulfinyl group, and on the nitrogen by a 2-(1-methylpiperidin-2-yl)ethyl group.
The benzenesulfonate salt of mesoridazine prepared using equimolar amounts of mesoridazine and benzenesulfonic acid.
A  glycopeptide antibiotic found in Streptomyces flavoviridis.

A member of the class of  xanthones that is 9H-xanthen-9-one substituted by a hydroxy group at position 1, a methyl group at position 8 and methoxy groups at positions 3 and 6. It has been isolated from the bark of Cupania cinerea.
A  hopanoid that is hopan-3-one substituted by an epoxy group across positions 17 and 21. It has been isolated from the bark of Cupania cinerea.
An  organic heteropentacyclic compound isolated from Aspergillus and Aspergillus ustus and has been shown to exhibit cytotoxic activity.
A pyrroloquinoline that is 3H-pyrrolo[2,3-c]quinoline substituted by a methyl group at position 4. It is a natural product found in Ohtaekwangia kribbensis and Rapidithrix thailandica.
A terminal acetylenic compound that is (17alpha)-17-ethynylestra-1(10),2,4-triene substituted by a methoxy group at position 3 and a hydroxy group at position 17.
A pyrroloquinoline that is 3H-pyrrolo[2,3-c]quinoline substituted by an isobutyl group at position 4. It is a natural product found in Ohtaekwangia kribbensis.
